Fixes #15594

This change adds type inference for schema-level  and options (like  and ) when these methods are
called without arguments.

Changes:
- Added 3 helper types to types/index.d.ts:
  - ResolveMethodOptions: Extracts method options from schema options
  - ApplyFlattenObjectIds: Applies ObjectId→string transformation
  - ApplyVersionKey: Removes __v field when versionKey: false

- Updated toObject() and toJSON() signatures in types/document.d.ts to use these helper types for proper type inference

The fix works correctly when using Schema.create() which properly infers all generic parameters including TSchemaOptions.

Example usage:
```typescript
const schema = Schema.create({
  testId: Types.ObjectId
}, {
  toObject: { flattenObjectIds: true, versionKey: false }
});

const Model = model('Test', schema);
const doc = new Model({...});

// Types are now correctly inferred!
const obj = doc.toObject(); // Type: { _id: string, testId: string, ... }
```

